By: Al-Ghazâlî
Reference:
  - Title: Qur'an
    Locus: XXVIII 28
---
Each thing hath two faces, a face of its own, and a face of its Lord; in
respect of its own face it is nothingness, and in respect of the Face of God
it is Being. Thus there is nothing in existence save only God and His Face,
for everything perisheth but His Face.
